+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772766164149,"sessionID":"ses_33ee723afffeODlU98WA5b1rWx","part":{"id":"prt_cc118f1e1001MZjS2rm9aRbrd2","sessionID":"ses_33ee723afffeODlU98WA5b1rWx","messageID":"msg_cc118ed56002lkXht9qKxlJsML","type":"tool","callID":"04001c354","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\napplyTo: \"**\"\n---\n\n# Ralph Plan for Full-Text Search Feature\n\n## Original Request\nAdd a full-text search feature to an existing Express + SQLite note‑taking API.\n\n- Implement `GET /notes/search?q=<query>` with:\n  - SQLite FTS5 across `title` and `body`\n  - BM25 ranking, snippet highlighting (`<mark>` tags)\n  - Phrase queries support (quoted strings)\n  - Pagination (20 per page via `page` param)\n  - Return `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n  - 400 error when `q` missing/empty\n- Implement `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>` returning up to 5 title suggestions matching the prefix in title or body.\n- Keep FTS index in sync with CRUD operations via SQLite triggers or manual sync.\n- Ensure all existing CRUD tests and new search tests pass.\n\n## Clarifications / Assumptions\n- SQLite version bundled with `better-sqlite3` supports FTS5 (common).\n- Highlighting will be done with SQLite `snippet` function on the body column (column index 1) and on title via separate highlight if needed – using body snippet is sufficient for tests.\n- Phrase queries are automatically handled by FTS5's MATCH operator when the query string contains quoted phrases.\n- Suggest endpoint can use simple `LIKE` prefix matching on both title and body.\n- The API returns JSON with proper status codes; validation errors use `ValidationError` class.\n- Seed data will automatically populate the FTS table via triggers.\n\n## Goal / Success Criteria\n- New endpoints exist and behave as described.\n- FTS virtual table `notes_fts` is created and kept in sync.\n- All existing 15 CRUD tests still pass.\n- All 20 new search tests pass (`npm test` returns exit code 0).\n- No lint or TypeScript errors.\n\n## Technical Approach\n1. **Database schema update** (`src/db.ts`)\n   - After creating `notes` table, create virtual FTS5 table:\n     ```sql\n     CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes_fts USING fts5(title, body, content='notes', content_rowid='id');\n     ```\n   - Add SQLite triggers for INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE on `notes` to keep `notes_fts` in sync.\n   - Triggers:\n     - `after insert` -> `INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);`\n     - `after delete` -> `DELETE FROM notes_fts WHERE rowid = old.id;`\n     - `after update` -> `UPDATE notes_fts SET title = new.title, body = new.body WHERE rowid = new.id;`\n2. **Routes** (`src/routes.ts`)\n   - Add two new route handlers under the same router.\n   - **Search handler** parses `q` and `page`, validates, performs two prepared statements:\n     - Count total matches.\n     - Retrieve paginated results with rank and snippet:\n       ```sql\n       SELECT notes.id, notes.title,\n              snippet(notes_fts, 1, '<mark>', '</mark>', '...', 10) AS snippet,\n              bm25(notes_fts) AS rank\n       FROM notes_fts JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n       WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n       ORDER BY rank\n       LIMIT ? OFFSET ?;\n       ```\n   - Return JSON shaped as required.\n   - **Suggest handler** validates `q`, runs:\n       ```sql\n       SELECT id, title FROM notes\n       WHERE title LIKE ? || '%' OR body LIKE ? || '%'\n       LIMIT 5;\n       ```\n     using lowercase for case‑insensitive match (`LOWER(title) LIKE LOWER(?) || '%'`).\n3. **Import necessary types** (`SearchResult`, `SuggestResult`) in `routes.ts`.\n4. **Update any TypeScript imports** to reference `.js` compiled output (already using .js extensions).\n5. **Run tests** to ensure everything works.\n6. **Add any needed npm packages** – none required beyond existing `better-sqlite3`.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/db.ts` – schema and triggers.\n- `src/routes.ts` – new endpoints and imports.\n- `src/models.ts` – already contains the result interfaces.\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| FTS5 not enabled in SQLite build used by better‑sqlite3. | Verify by executing a quick SQLite query after creating the virtual table; if it fails, fallback to manual `LIKE` search (unlikely in modern builds). |\n| Triggers not firing for updates that only change tags. | Triggers only update title/body; tags are irrelevant for full‑text search, so no impact. |\n| Snippet function may produce `null` if no match in body. | Use `COALESCE(snippet, '')` or fallback to empty string. |\n| Pagination edge cases (page too high). | Return empty `results` array; total still accurate.\n\n## Execution Plan (Task List)\n1. Create plan file (done).\n2. Add FTS5 table and triggers in `src/db.ts`.\n3. Implement search route in `src/routes.ts`.\n4. Implement suggest route in `src/routes.ts`.\n5. Adjust imports for new types.\n6. Run `npm test` – fix any TypeScript or runtime errors.\n7. Ensure seed data populates FTS via triggers.\n8. Commit changes.\n9. Mark loop complete.\n\n---\n*End of plan.*"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772766164141,"end":1772766164148}}}}
